Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @Shallot{1%unit}; thinly slice one half and mince remaining. Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise.

Place potatoes in a #large pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; then drain and return potatoes to #pot.

While potatoes cook, in a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, minced shallot, half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), and 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings); season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Form mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

Place meatloaves on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Add a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}. Toss Brussels sprouts on empty side with a drizzle of oil; season generously with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Line sheet with foil first for easier cleanup.

Roast on top rack until meatloaves are cooked through and Brussels sprouts are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast meatloaves on middle rack and Brussels sprouts on top rack. If Brussels sprouts finish first, remove from sheet and continue roasting meatloaves.

While everything roasts, strip thyme leaves from @Thyme{1/4%ounce}(chopped) stems; finely chop leaves until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chopped thyme and sliced shallot; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1%unit} and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup water for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in half the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step) and @Butter{2%tablespoon} until melted and combined. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat pot with drained potatoes over low heat; add @Butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining sour cream, and remaining garlic powder.

Mash until smooth and creamy with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

If necessary, reheat pan with sauce over low heat; stir until warmed through.

Divide meatloaves, mashed potatoes, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Spoon sauce over meatloaves and serve.